gov.nasa.arc.brahms.vm.api.events
Interface IMoveContinuedFromImpasseEM

All Superinterfaces:
IActivityEventConstants, IEventMessage, IMoveEventConstants, java.io.Serializable
public interface IMoveContinuedFromImpasseEM
extends IEventMessage, IMoveEventConstants

The IMoveContinuedFromImpasseEM event message is send to the event notifier for every move activity that is continued after the activity was impassed.

The contents of this event (property name - type):

  • IMoveContinuedFromImpasseEM.ACTIVITYCTX - a MoveActivityCtx (object property)
  • IMoveContinuedFromImpasseEM.STATECTX - an ActivityStateCtx (object property)
  • IMoveContinuedFromImpasseEM.EVENTTIME - the time of the event (long property)
  • IMoveContinuedFromImpasseEM.STARTLOCATION - a ParameterCtx (object property)

Version:
27 September 2000

Ron van Hoof
